** Title: **

Mission Planning Technical Specialist

** Your KBR future – delivering solutions and changing the world **

** About KBR: **

** We are a company of innovators, thinkers, creators, explorers, volunteers and dreamers who all share one goal — to improve the world. **

KBR delivers science, technology and engineering solutions to governments and
companies around the world. KBR employs approximately 34,000 people performing
diverse, complex, and mission-critical roles in 33 countries.

For 65 years, KBR and its heritage companies are proud to have delivered some
of Australia’s largest and most complex projects.

With around 2,000 employees in 6 primary offices throughout Australia, we are
committed to social and environmental sustainability and delivering projects
with a digital mindset driving innovation within our business and for our
customers.

We help ensure mission success on land, in the air, at sea, in space and
cyberspace for our defence customers. From individual technologies and
services to comprehensive project delivery and mission execution, no other
company can match the breadth and depth of KBR.

KBR comprises a diverse team who provide a broad spectrum of capabilities
across Australia and the Asia Pacific. Our proven project teams readily
address complex and multi-disciplinary activities, providing low-risk and
cost-effective solutions to the defence force.

Learn more about our business here.

** The Opportunity: **

We are currently seeking Expression of Interests from highly motivated Mission
Planning Technical Specialist with Aviation Mission Planning experience who
will join our team to provide technical expertise and advice to support the
Aviation Mission Planning Team.

The Mission Planning Technical SMEs would provide technical expertise and
advice to support with implementation of mission planning system requirements
by providing design and implementation guidance.

The Mission Planning Technical SME would also provide expertise and guidance
relating to future requirements for Aviation Mission Planning and integration
into a broader implementation strategy.

All candidates will be required to hold and maintain an active NV1 clearance.
Only candidates holding an NV1 clearance or above should apply.

The Mission Planning Technical SME would be responsible to the Aviation
Mission Planning Systems Team Lead to provide technical support for
deliverables, and represent Aviation Mission Planning Team as follows:

  * Provide specialist advice for mission planning design and integration for fixed and deployed computer networks. 

  * Provide technical advice in relation to the system hardware and software. 

  * Provide technical expertise to support the development of mission planning elements and the integration of the Aviation Mission Planning with other Defence planning, co-ordination and reporting systems. 

  * Provide specialist advice to acquisitions projects for Aviation Mission Planning interfaces. 

  * Maintaining knowledge of allied forces development and employment of Aviation Mission Planning System, through attendance at technical forums such as Interface Control Working Group (ICWG) meetings and through review of documentation supplied by allied forces. 

